  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 70ee8ab7554a13a4d9d7566ffc03ae8b, type: 3}
  m_Name: Social Conundrum
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FlightPaper.ProjectSorrow.Encounters.EncounterScriptableObject
  id: 7
  title: Social Conundrum
  description: 'A random stranger strikes up a conversation with you. They seem nice
    enough, but your mind begins to wander.


    There''s a lull in the conversation.
    The stranger is waiting for you to respond, but you missed whatever they said.'
  options:
  - title: Smile and nod
    description: <color=red>-1</color> confidence
    conclusion: 'You hope that if you simply nod along, they won''t notice how lost
      you are. '
    isHidden: 0
    item: {fileID: 0}
    consumable: {fileID: 0}
    tag: 
  - title: Change the subject
    description: <color=red>-3</color> reputation
    conclusion: 'Unsure how to respond, you change the subject to something else
      entirely.


      They appear somewhat annoyed with you, but at least you know
      what''s being talked about now. '
    isHidden: 0
    item: {fileID: 0}
    consumable: {fileID: 0}
    tag: Reputation
  - title: Ask them to repeat themself
    description: <color=red>-00:20.00</color>
    conclusion: 'You feel like it''s the honest thing to do, but now they''re retelling
      their entire story. '
    isHidden: 0
    item: {fileID: 0}
    consumable: {fileID: 0}
    tag: 
  minRound: 0
  rarity: 0
